              cmap='Blues',

Out[ ]:
'GEOGCS["WGS 84",DATUM["WGS_1984",SPHEROID["WGS 84",6378137,298.257223563,AUTHORITY["EPSG","7030"]],AUTHORITY["EPSG","6326"]],PRIMEM["Greenwich",0],UNIT["degree",0.0174532925199433,AUTHORITY["EPSG","9122"]],AXIS["Latitude",NORTH],AXIS["Longitude",EAST],AUTHORITY["EPSG","4326"]]'
In [ ]:
# Metadata for rows and columns; Number of bands
x_size, y_size, n_bands = g.RasterXSize, g.RasterYSize, g.RasterCount
data = g.ReadAsArray()
# Handler to a driver
driver = gdal.GetDriverByName("HFA")
In [ ]:
dataset_out = driver.Create("Data_02/Onondaga_DEM_gdal.img", x_size, y_size, n_bands, gdal.GDT_Byte)
In [ ]:
# Output Geotransform
dataset_out.SetGeoTransform (g.GetGeoTransform())
# Output Projection
dataset_out.SetProjection(g.GetProjectionRef())
# Write our data array to band 1; must have matching types
dataset_out.GetRasterBand(1).WriteArray(data)
# Shuts down GDAL, closes the file, and writes to it
dataset_out = None
